--- CompleteMazeBuilder Torch Prefab Assignment Fix - 2026-03-04
+++ Assets/Scripts/Core/06_Maze/CompleteMazeBuilder.cs

ISSUE:
======
LightPlacementEngine requires torchPrefab to be assigned, but it was not being
set by CompleteMazeBuilder, causing torches to not spawn.

ROOT CAUSE:
===========
LightPlacementEngine.LoadAndInstantiateTorches() checks if torchPrefab is null:
  if (torchPrefab == null) {
      Debug.LogError("❌ Please assign torchPrefab in Inspector!");
      return;
  }

CompleteMazeBuilder was not assigning the torch prefab before calling
LoadAndInstantiateTorches().

FIX APPLIED:
============
Added code to get torchHandlePrefab from TorchPool and assign it to
LightPlacementEngine's torchPrefab field via reflection.

CHANGES:
========

Added in PlaceTorches():
```csharp
// Assign torch prefab from TorchPool to LightPlacementEngine
var torchPrefabField = typeof(LightPlacementEngine).GetField(
    "torchPrefab", BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance);
if (torchPrefabField != null)
{
    // Try to get torchHandlePrefab from TorchPool
    var torchHandleField = typeof(TorchPool).GetField(
        "torchHandlePrefab", BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance);
    if (torchHandleField != null)
    {
        var torchHandlePrefab = torchHandleField.GetValue(torchPool) as GameObject;
        if (torchHandlePrefab != null)
        {
            torchPrefabField.SetValue(lightPlacementEngine, torchHandlePrefab);
            Debug.Log($"[CompleteMazeBuilder] 🎆 Assigned torch prefab: {torchHandlePrefab.name}");
        }
    }
}
```

